One interesting idea (for JS) is defining functions as pattern matches on the arguments. Here's a factorial from the docs:<p><pre><code>    >>> var factorial = wu.match(
    ...   [ 0 ],      1,
    ...   [ Number ], function (n) { return n * factorial(n - 1); }
    ... );
    >>> factorial(5);
    120</code></pre>
